<br>
That said, I also remember that if you had the buff but not the pet up and got caught in an AE, it would sometimes respawn the pet. I also remember that if you zoned or relogged while invis, you would have the buff, pet, and invis all running when you loaded in, so it IS possible, they just need to stop it from poofing when you cast an invis. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uatabex.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Atabex</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/8/02 4:54:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm33.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=46.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Familiar poofing on invis</span><hr size=1> Shard, guess you missed the point so here it is for the Umpteenth time. Why do we have the only mana-regen that can be killed and can also be removed by the cancel maigc line of spells? Yes, we get other bonus's for having the effect (Resists, Mana pool, see invis) but other classes mana regens also get additional Effects.<br>
<br>
Cleric: Increase Hitpoints by 294 - 300, Increase AC by 30<br>
Druid: Increase AC (24), Increase Hitpoints (450)<br>
Magician: Increase Health Regen (5 per tick), Increase AC (24) <br>
<br>
In addition, if the familiar is slain by an AE you loose additional mana (40-60 %) or was this changed? I find myself using the familiar alot less these days, alot.<br>
<br>
So our mana regen:<br>
1. Drops when we invis. (to be fixed)<br>
2. Drops when we Evac<br>
3. Can be killed and if it is we loose additional mana.<br>
4. The regen is lower then the Druid or Cleric regens and only the 60 lvl Wiz regen is better then the Magician mana regen.<br>
<br>
Oh, I see the player balance in this, sorry I was so mistaken. I'll try not to whine so much in the future.<br>
<br>
Oh by the way, did you miss the point that resists are for when you get cast on, so if you are fighting a top end mob that doesn't cast the bonus to resists are just fluff.<br>
<br>
Wonder how many times I have to stress the point that I'm wondering if people think our familiars are balanced to other classes mana regens not wether they mind if it drops because you evac or not. <p><font size=1 color=red><MARQUEE BEHAVIOR="scroll"  SCROLLDELAY="4" SCROLLAMOUNT="4">SPIDER MAN GONNA KICK YOUR @$$ !!!!!!<font size=4 color=red></MARQUEE>
 </font>

 
<br>
Atabex [
<A HREF=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=52192 target="_blank"> My Stuff</A> ]
<br>
60 lvl Sorcerer
<br>Evermore Guildleader
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utojizimitz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tojizimitz</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_yellowspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/8/02 5:16:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm33.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=46.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Familiar poofing on invis</span><hr size=1> Yes Familiars need to be fixed, using boatloads of mana through fizzles, to cast our only self mana regen, (not including BoF) and then lose it through invising, evacing or AoEs from mobs seems rather harsh when compared to other classes.  <br>
<br>
So put your points into AA and get the Improved Familiar?  Well I did and guess what?  The see invis component is broken and he gives absolutely no extra mana or mana regen.  He improves your resists and he resists AoEs, that's it.  .   From the sound of it, this is what Verant intended when they created this Alt Exp Familiar,  but it makes no sense to me that the &quot;Improved&quot; familiar isn't as good as the Greater Familiar.<br>
<br>
Apparently he has been changed on the test server to include mana and mana regen, nothing about his see invis being broken though, and no word yet whether or not the changes are going live.<br>
<br>
**  Edit **  With the patch msg today 5/8 it looks like they might have fixed the Improved Familiar, all it says is that Improved familiars should now be better than Greater Familiar but no details.<br>
<br>
 <p><img src=http://www.eqguild.net/guilds/thesilentwatch/tojizimitz.jpg></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utojizimitz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tojizimitz</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_yellowspot.gif" BORDER=0> at: 5/8/02 5:48:03 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ushardanaan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shardanaan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/14/02 8:43:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm33.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=46.topic&index=27>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Familiar poofing on invis</span><hr size=1> Ok, Atabex, let me address a couple of things here.<br>
<br>
First of all, I wasn't addressing your points about balance in regards to other classes.  I was addressing those people who were saying that the familiar in and of itself was not worth casting.<br>
<br>
In regards to class balance, I don't think it's particularly valid to compare a familiar to any AC / HP buff, since it's not intended for that in any regard.<br>
<br>
As far as the comparison to mask of the hunter / stalker and the cleric regen lines, yeah, I'd agree that familiars are underpowered.  While mask of the hunter is outdoor only, mask of the stalker does put druids above us on mana regen.<br>
<br>
The only real problem I see with this is the assumption of a wizard having Epic mana regen.  With that on top of our familiar, we're clearly above any other classes (save enches) self-mana buff.  The problem then is one of the disadvantages of familiars.<br>
<br>
Even though it's now been changed back, making this a moot point, I still rarely ever had a problem with losing the familiar.  If we were in Umbral, we'd invis to one of the caves or whatnot, drop invis, summon familiar.  In general, I don't think most of us invis after we're where we're going.  As for the pet loss on evac, yeah, that was stupid.<br>
<br>
The question became one of usefulness against AE mobs, which they've again eliminated any disadvantages that familiars had by allowing /pet get lost.<br>
<br>
Of course I like the change, and it makes sense since that's when you need resists the most, but *if* a wizard has epic regen with the familiar, it's as good or better than the druid / cleric / mage self-buffs.<br>
<br>
I think that's what they're assuming, and it's rather assinine for them to do.  The regen should probably be higher than it is, given the extra cost / difficulty, but I see it as a perk more than anything else.  I dealt fine back when all I had available was Clarity 2 and the epic, so I find it difficult to complain about the extra mana regen coming out my ears that I've got now.<br>
<br>
On a side note, there IS something broken about the level 54 familiar--I'd go through a good five or six fizzles to cast it, but as soon as I nabbed a copy of greater fam, I get maybe one fizzle every four casts or so.<br>
<br>
Anyway, getting off topic...my only point was that the familiars were still useful, not that they were particularly balanced against other classes' self-mana regen buffs.  At level 60, I'd be inclined to agree, given the numbers.<br>
<br>
At any earlier level, no one else even has lower level equivelents of Mask of the hunter / (insert buff here).  So, mebbe they just need to look at us sorcerers.<br>
<br>
